Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.09,0:00:10.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine.\NWord is that Lord Alexis has been attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.38,0:00:13.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.80,0:00:16.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, he apparently\Nsuffered no injuries, and is now safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.06,0:00:18.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That so?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.56,0:00:22.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The details are still unclear,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.23,0:00:26.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems he was caught\Nin the crosshairs of some Union in-fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.03,0:00:32.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't the people\Nbehind my father's assassination?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.70,0:00:38.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Alexis!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:43.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why now, after the incident in the Great Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:50.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis has expressed his desire to speak\Nwith you, no matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.34,0:00:53.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you consider hearing him out?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.13,0:00:56.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father's assassination\Nwas a premeditated plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.64,0:01:05.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those who were against our marriage\Ntriggered that tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.94,0:01:08.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.07,0:01:14.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were never meant to\Nbe together, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.54,0:02:53.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.96,0:02:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To plot an assassination\Nis a bold move for Lord Pederico.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.09,0:03:00.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:04.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I suspected, the marquis\Nis still in love with Marrine, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:06.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It did seem that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.93,0:03:11.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you two know how\Nthe marquis and Marrine first met?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:12.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.31,0:03:15.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I've heard is that they met\Nwhile studying in Eramu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.07,0:03:20.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. That's where they fell in love,\Nsix years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:28.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:32.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a man sitting in the middle of the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.46,0:03:34.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by his outfit,\NI'd say the son of a Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:44.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a public carriage road.\NKindly abstain from such reckless behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:48.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The cobblestones used to pave\Nthis road are so very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reflecting the sunlight, sparkling and lovely!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.57,0:04:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.91,0:04:06.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've known the word "love".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But after seeing you,\Nfor the first time, I now know what it means!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:22.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your favorite pick-up line?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.52,0:04:33.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My lady, a letter has arrived for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:37.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it from that young man again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:40.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Please put it away.\N- Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.15,0:04:47.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you could read just one,\Nand decline his advances in a letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.79,0:04:49.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:05.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I am enveloped in\Nthe joy of discovering what love is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:10.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is what moves me.\NTonight, I will deliver flowers to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:13.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:16.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean a messenger\Nwill be arriving shortly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:29.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are those roses?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.45,0:05:34.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, Lord Alexis appeared,\Nsaying he'd come to bring you flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.33,0:05:36.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then suddenly started\Nlining up those stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:37.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.71,0:05:42.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's a bit odd, but interesting, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:46.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'll need to thank him for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.30,0:05:52.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis often attends soirées\Nwhere the sons of Lords gather, I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well! You're a new face here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:13.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your hair is lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.25,0:06:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your hips are so slender,\NI'm dying to put my arms around them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:25.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind not touching me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.72,0:06:28.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in you whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.89,0:06:30.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,H-How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.39,0:06:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.10,0:06:39.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Alexis?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This young lady doesn't want your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.73,0:06:45.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't try to force yourself on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:49.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you! Stay out of my business!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:56.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.06,0:07:22.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:26.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I dreaming, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:28.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:30.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your wound must hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:36.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we've met again, I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.83,0:07:40.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're Jalucia's Prince of the Sun,\NAlexis, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I know who you are, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:48.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But still, why did you come to this soirée?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:52.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You gave me such lovely flowers,\Nso I wanted to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.51,0:07:58.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew about my family,\Nso why did you fall in love with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:01.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In Eramu, family names mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.10,0:08:06.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I met you, my heart skipped a beat,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.57,0:08:08.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I realized it was love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.74,0:08:15.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you and I are enemies\Nwho can never be united.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:20.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true, but I can't resist\Na heart that now knows love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.50,0:08:23.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I could sense how you felt\Njust by reading your letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:27.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was like reading the script\Nof a romantic play!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.51,0:08:32.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But... it's a play that will end in tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.27,0:08:47.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is my thanks for the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.07,0:08:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's my first kiss ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not that you have to treasure it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:08:59.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's end this right now,\Nas I have no intention of seeing you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.91,0:09:02.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.29,0:09:06.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I will never forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:11.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because all that you are\Nis now inscribed in my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:36.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were heading\Nto Lord Darcy's mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:41.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My lady, please look outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.37,0:09:45.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it again, one last time! Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:46.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.25,0:09:48.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.46,0:09:52.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Twinkle, twinkle, little star...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:57.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}How I wonder what you are...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:55.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What were you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.51,0:09:57.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared to be rebuked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.34,0:10:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Up above the world so high...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.76,0:10:03.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's just... I could no longer bear\Nseeing you so crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:06.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Like a diamond in the sky...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.52,0:10:05.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd call that unsolicited concern!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not very far\Nfrom where Lord Alexis lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}Twinkle, twinkle, little star...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:15.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\i1}How I wonder what you are...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:15.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's been known to come here by foot,\Nand interact with the children like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:17.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.74,0:10:21.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, everyone,\Nnow take your silver coins, and head on home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.16,0:10:22.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:25.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Here.\N- Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:27.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:29.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that his idea of interacting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:33.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Alexis!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.06,0:10:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You do realize\Nthat you'll lead the Union one day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:49.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yet here you are,\Nhanding out silver coins to children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.02,0:10:53.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it gives you satisfaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.94,0:10:57.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you start giving charity to some,\Nthere will inequity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:10:59.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it will gradually\Nundermine your sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:02.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.91,0:11:06.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't see what I'm doing as charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.96,0:11:12.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, they only did it\Nfor the money I gave them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:13.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not how it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.50,0:11:17.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now they look forward to singing together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.22,0:11:19.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.14,0:11:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Charity is the act of giving\Nmoney or things, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.01,0:11:27.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The recipient may feel gratitude,\Nbut there's no joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:31.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For someone to live in bliss,\Ntheir heart must be filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:34.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is not a Lord's duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:36.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:40.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, I think it to be\Nthe most important thing of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:45.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If a sovereign has forgotten that,\Nhe'll eventually bring his people grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.49,0:11:47.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.25,0:11:50.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...just an ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.33,0:11:54.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if attaining that ideal is an arduous path,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:58.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as long as you keep pursuing it,\Nyou can certainly get closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it you're able to say that\Nwith such conviction?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because those children smile\Nwhen they're with me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A sovereign who fills people's hearts...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.78,0:12:25.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.63,0:12:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What have you decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:41.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be your queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.43,0:12:47.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I have fallen in love with you as well,\Nso it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.31,0:12:50.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how long it will take.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I promise to come for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:57.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So don't ever have a change of heart,\Nand wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.07,0:12:58.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.78,0:13:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll wait for you!\NAnd I would never have a change of heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.28,0:13:06.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because no one but you can fill my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.33,0:13:17.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I know\Nof how their romance began.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:21.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would've been against a political marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if they truly love one another,\Nthey should be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.89,0:13:28.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:41.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then we agree, Pederico Rossini's penalty\Nwill be expulsion from the Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.44,0:13:42.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No objection!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:47.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, next on the agenda\Nis Lord Dawson's proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.12,0:13:50.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I find the Earl of Altirk's actions\Nto be highly questionable!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:57.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since you took it upon yourself to\Ngo to war against the Factory Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.71,0:14:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a truce no longer looks likely,\Nand the Union is in crisis!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.13,0:14:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.88,0:14:06.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the circumstances\Nbehind that battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:10.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have my vassal, Theo Cornaro,\Nexplain it all to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:11.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:13.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.06,0:14:18.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've repeatedly sought the allegiance\Nof Lord Pavel of Starck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:21.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but have yet to receive an answer.\NWhat's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:27.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allegiance cannot be for form's sake.\NThere must also be an emotional connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not something so easily pledged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.62,0:14:34.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning he can't recognize\Nsomeone of my caliber as his master?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:36.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What he means is that he cannot at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:40.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should you show him\Nthat you are equipped to lead the Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.79,0:14:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my Lord will feel assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.30,0:14:46.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So he's telling me to\Nfirst prove that I'm equipped?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:51.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're seeking my Lord's allegiance\Nat this time, that's what he wishes you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:57.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:03.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The crucial point is that the battle Theo set off\Nwasn't against the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:07.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Banishing a Lord who'd run afoul\Nof the court rank system,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:10.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and seizing his court rank and lands\Nwas a justified action.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, mages in attendance?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:24.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then, it was the Alliance\Nwho launched an attack on Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:29.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you aren't suggesting\Nhe not fight back under enemy attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.30,0:15:33.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Announcing himself as a member of the Union\Nwhile surrounded by Alliance forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.43,0:15:36.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder he was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.68,0:15:38.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.10,0:15:42.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's no wonder my Altirk\Ncame under Alliance attack, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:44.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop twisting my words!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.82,0:15:48.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Dawson, please calm yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:54.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I admit that it was the Alliance\Nwho set off the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.33,0:15:56.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you hadn't lent a helping hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.49,0:15:59.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,our relationship with the Alliance\Nwouldn't have soured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.04,0:16:04.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until the moment Waldlind intervened,\Nthat might've been the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Waldlind rejected Theo Cornaro\Nwhen he sought to join the Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:12.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and sent their knights after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.01,0:16:15.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the reason why he requested my aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.72,0:16:18.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should've just ignored him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:21.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was your arbitrary decision\Nwhich set off that battle with the Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.73,0:16:24.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- That's right!\N- Don't try to rationalize it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.36,0:16:29.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should've just ignored him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.95,0:16:34.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I love the Fantasia Union,\Nwhich prizes freedom and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.62,0:16:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason, I want to protect\Nanyone who joins the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.41,0:16:45.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If any one of you here came under attack,\NI guarantee that I will come to your aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.46,0:16:52.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,\Nthe small, neutral continent of Bredland,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:56.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is about to be attacked by the Sea King Erik.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.68,0:16:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the Union as a whole...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.68,0:17:02.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the only option is to thwart him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:04.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't agree more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.90,0:17:09.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should we be denounced for having\Nprotected Sievis, now part of the Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:14.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My astute fellow Lords, please consider\Nthe overall interests of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.37,0:17:18.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the clincher.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:22.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now this conference\Nis under Sir Villar's control.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:23.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I now know where you all stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.46,0:17:28.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We, the Fantasia Union, will confront\Nthe Factory Alliance with military might.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:31.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does everyone agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.17,0:17:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I see no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:34.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No objection.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.55,0:17:36.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No objection...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.35,0:17:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I'd rather not\Ngo to war with the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.52,0:17:42.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'll comply with today's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.10,0:17:48.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, there's one thing\NI'd like to propose, if I may.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:54.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I only became your leader\Nbecause my father was an Archduke.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:18:00.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now I think we should choose the man\Nwho's best-suited to lead the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.91,0:18:07.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we've decided to\Ntake on the Alliance in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:12.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe no one is more suited to be leader\Nof the Union than the Earl of Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.63,0:18:16.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if the Earl of Altirk\Ndoes become our leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:20.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to be the first to offer\Nmy services to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.23,0:18:29.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the birth of Archduke Villar Constance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.15,0:18:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.23,0:18:32.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I lose this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.03,0:18:34.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:40.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although I'm honored by\Nyour endorsement, Lord Alexis,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I respectfully decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.41,0:18:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.00,0:18:55.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt my grandfather, Jurgen Kreische,\Nwould want to see his grandchildren fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:01.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was Jurgen Kreische, the Blood-and-Iron Earl,\Nwho founded the Factory Alliance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:11.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Fantasia Union was created to counter it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:18.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And half of the blood running\Nin Lord Villar's veins is Kreische blood.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:26.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that the Marquis of Jalucia\Nis the best man to lead the Union, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.41,0:19:27.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No objection!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.42,0:19:31.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And since we've chosen\Nthe Marquis of Jalucia as our leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.17,0:19:34.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we should\Npursue peace talks with the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.26,0:19:37.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Alliance will never accept peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.72,0:19:41.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They'll bolster their forces,\Nand we'll soon be under attack, without fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.30,0:19:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you still want to proceed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.56,0:19:46.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, are you going\Nto defy the will of our leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.35,0:19:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't acknowledged this yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:52.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then would you like to\Nbecome leader yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.61,0:19:59.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, once again,\Ndoes anyone object to peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.45,0:20:01.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No objections!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Union has squandered\Na golden opportunity to destroy the Alliance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.05,0:20:21.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This time around, Waldlind is sure to\Nattack the Union with their pride at stake.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.39,0:20:24.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will Altirk be able to withstand it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:32.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A messenger from the Union\Nhas proposed peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.15,0:20:33.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.52,0:20:39.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First Sievis, and if that wasn't enough\Nthey seize Forbes and Clovis,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.15,0:20:40.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and now they seek peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:42.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't blame you for being angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.78,0:20:48.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but the Union wishes to follow the agenda\Nagreed upon before the Great Hall Tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:50.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The agenda under which\NI'd marry the Marquis of Jalucia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.96,0:20:53.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,uniting the families of the two Archdukes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:54.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:20:58.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That seems to be the will of Alexis Doucet,\Nleader of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:05.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to tell Gerhart\Nto prepare for battle with Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.68,0:21:08.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He likely has no intention of serving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.31,0:21:10.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be taking part as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.64,0:21:16.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use the conquest of Starck\Nas a foothold to invade Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.07,0:21:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.44,0:21:56.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Alexis...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:05.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,THE CONGRESS DANCES
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.12,0:23:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 9:\NTHE BLACK PRINCESS
